     <p><strong>Serving Society</strong><br> Outside of a service-oriented internship, students have the option of fulfilling the Competent and Compassionate Action area of the GE requirement another way.<br> By enrolling in APP-191SS (Serving Society for zero credits) in advance of the service, a student participates in a minimum of 12 hours of <strong>community service</strong> over the course of the semester. Does your organization have a project or need that may be met by a student volunteer? The student's hours are documented and his or her work is evaluated by a supervisor in the community. On this end, some reading and written reflection is required. Participating organizations may post volunteer opportunities on <a href="https://westmont-csm.symplicity.com/employers/">Job Spot</a>. </p> 
     <h5>Deadline for Spring 2015 Internship Registration</h5> 
     <p>Registration for spring internship courses is November 17th-20th, 2014.<span style="font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"> <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">The ILAF must be submitted by Friday at 3:30 pm on January 30, 2015.</b></span> This means students planning to do a spring internship or major practicum for academic credit need to secureno later than Thursday, January 29, 2015.</p> 
     <p>For more information, please contact Ms. Jennifer Taylor, Director of Internships (jmtaylor@westmont.edu).</p> 
